President Barack Obama has proclaimed January 2016 as National Mentoring Month in the United States. The proclamation recognizes the importance of mentors in providing resources and support to young people, and emphasizes the need for a society in which all mentors and mentees can thrive in learning relationships. The President encourages Americans to become mentors and highlights initiatives such as My Brother's Keeper and Reach Higher that aim to connect youth with effective mentoring programs. The proclamation also celebrates the achievements of young people and calls for support and recognition of their potential.